I'd like to speak about the change of strategie. This time, clerics came in the lair with their group. <br>
<br>
I had 3 melees to heal, I used remedy - a 'small' but fast and mana efficient heal. No melee die before me. When I finaly aggro Vox, I was down to 10mana and had about 1 bubble life left due to the AE. I had time to reload my heal, buff MR and CR and come back in the lair for some more heals. None of my melee died in the meanwhile. I lost my main melee when he aggro Vox quite hard and I had no CH reloaded at this time. He died 5s before Vox herself die <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
On the other Vox raids I was in, healing in the triage area, I saw my melee groupmates falling much sooner. As far as I can compare, I think this strategie rocks! <p><table>
